      <Notes><![CDATA[The Total Carbon Column Observing Network (TCCON) is a network of ground-based Fourier Transform Spectrometers that record spectra of the sun in the near-infrared. From these spectra, accurate and precise column-averaged abundances of atmospheric constituents including CO2, CH4, N2O, HF, CO, H2O, and HDO, are retrieved.

Support for the network is provided in part by NASA through grants made to the California Institute of Technology.  Support for analysis and operations at the individual sites are described on the site pages.]]></Notes>
